{
  "name": "@aliran/core",
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "description": "Aliran shared crypto: OPRF login, Argon2id verifiers, key wrapping",
  "license": "MIT",
  "type": "module",
  "main": "index.js",
  "exports": {
    ".": "./index.js",
    "./oprf.js": "./oprf.js",
    "./password.js": "./password.js",
    "./keybox.js": "./keybox.js",
    "./pow.js": "./pow.js",
    "./token.js": "./token.js",
    "./net-tune.js": "./net-tune.js",
    "./store-gc.js": "./store-gc.js",
    "./package.json": "./package.json"
  },
  "files": [
    "index.js",
    "oprf.js",
    "password.js",
    "keybox.js",
    "pow.js",
    "token.js",
    "net-tune.js",
    "store-gc.js",
    "README.md"
  ],
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "git+https://github.com/AbueloSimpson/aliran.git",
    "directory": "core"
  },
  "homepage": "https://abuelosimpson.github.io/aliran/",
  "bugs": "https://github.com/AbueloSimpson/aliran/issues",
  "keywords": [
    "oprf",
    "argon2id",
    "crypto",
    "p2p",
    "holepunch",
    "aliran"
  ],
  "engines": {
    "node": ">=20"
  },
  "publishConfig": {
    "access": "public"
  },
  "scripts": {
    "test": "node test.mjs"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "@noble/curves": "^1.6.0",
    "@noble/hashes": "^1.5.0",
    "b4a": "^1.6.6",
    "sodium-native": "^4.3.0"
  },
  "comment": "OPRF group math uses the audited @noble/curves ristretto255 (sodium-native in this build lacks ristretto ops). Argon2id + secretbox use sodium-native. Have the crypto independently reviewed before production. net-tune.js and store-gc.js are deliberately NOT re-exported by index.js — server components import them by path (they are Node/Bare infra helpers, not crypto)."
}
